parts.text:
```json
{
"application": "LSF",
"software": [
"CMSSW",
"scramv1",
"cmsStage"
],
"resources": [
"SCRATCH",
"AFS",
"input file (Input.root)",
"output files (Output[1-20].root)"
]
}
```

This script is running on a **LSF** (Load Sharing Facility) cluster, as indicated by the `#BSUB` directives. The script utilizes a **CMSSW** (CMSSW is a software framework used by the CMS experiment at CERN) software environment, using **scramv1** to set up the correct environment for the CMSSW release.  It also utilizes the **cmsStage** utility for transferring input and output files. The script relies on files stored in the **AFS** (Andrew File System) and utilizes **SCRATCH** disk space for temporary files. The input file is named **Input.root**, and multiple output files, named **Output[1-20].root**, are generated.
